the out put of git status is very comprehensive,
but it's wordy (it's have too words!)

we can use git status -s  ("s" stand for short)
it just brief the status!

short status have two column in result (in left side)
LEFT ONE FOR STAGE AREA
RIGHT ONE FOR WORKING DIRECTORY


MODIFYING FILES

when we modify an existing file we get:
 M "src/section_2/git ignore 8"  (left column is empty)
it means we have some changes (modifying) on working directory -------> right column is M
it means we have no change on stage                            ------->left column is empty

if we add it to stage (git add .) :
M  "src/section_2/git ignore 8"  (right column is empty)
it means we no changes on working directory                    -------> right column is empty
it means we have modify some file stage                        -------> left column is M

if we edite something new on file before commiting pre stage
MM  "src/section_2/git ignore 8"  (right column is empty)
it means we have some changes (modifying) on working directory -------> right column is M
it means we have modify some file stage                        -------> left column is M
(we should create a new snapshot on stage (git add .))


